@Marcus_Oakley's recent body of work focuses on a black and white view of the outside. He uses these drawings as a way to record his time and memories of these things and places. From mid-century housing to tranquil forests, Marcus minimally depicts these settings in his usual charming style. ⠀
∙⠀
“I often drift from colour to black and white depending on my mood, so it doesn’t specifically feel like I’m making a decision, more a melodic meteorological shift in melody. I like the simplicity and minimalism of using a pen and a piece of paper, and the challenge of just drawing lines to hopefully make a successful drawing I’m happy with.” #itsnicethat
